<section xml:id="sec-introducing-the-derivative">
  <title>Introducing the Derivative</title>

  <!-- Content summary: Understand the limit definition of a derivative: lim h -> 0 (f(x+h) - f(x))/h The derivative of a function 𝑓⁡(𝑥) at a point 𝑥=𝑎 is the slope of the tangent line to the curve 𝑓⁡(𝑥) at 𝑥=𝑎. The derivative of 𝑓⁡(𝑥) at 𝑥=𝑎 is written 𝑓′⁡(𝑎). The derivative 𝑓′⁡(𝑎) measures how the curve changes at the point (𝑎,𝑓⁡(𝑎)). The derivative 𝑓′⁡(𝑎) may be thought of as the instantaneous rate of change of the function 𝑓⁡(𝑥) at 𝑥=𝑎 - Introduce dy/dx notation -->

  <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li>Determine the derivatives of polynomial functions</li>
    </ul>
  </objectives>

